      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) Mechanistic basis (how it would block)\nMost small-molecule hERG blockers bind in the **inner cavity** of the channel (accessible from the cytosolic side when open/inactivated). This molecule has:\n- A **permanently/strongly protonated nitrogen** (as drawn) that can serve as the **cationic \u201canchor\u201d**.\n- A **bulky aromatic system** that can occupy the hydrophobic cavity and engage in **\u03c0/hydrophobic interactions**, stabilizing a non-conducting state (functional block).",
