      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 4) 3D/conformation considerations (explicitly addressing the hard part)\n- The **basic center is in a cyclic amine**, which restricts conformations but still allows the N-substituent to project outward.\n- The **aromatic system is fused/rigid and likely planar**, which often fits well into the elongated hERG cavity.\n- The **N\u2013aryl attachment** is relatively short; depending on torsion constraints, the aromatic \u201ctail\u201d may be positioned favorably for cavity occupancy. Nothing in the 2D structure suggests severe steric prevention of a binding pose.\n- The **alcohol** may introduce an H-bond with solvent and slightly bias orientation, but it\u2019s not a strong \u201canti-hERG\u201d feature by itself.",
