      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 5) Verification / uncertainty check\n- **No contradiction** with the canonical hERG blocker motif: it has (i) a strong basic center and (ii) substantial aromatic hydrophobe.\n- **Main uncertainty:** actual hERG potency depends strongly on **logP/logD, pKa distribution (mono- vs dication), and precise 3D alignment**. If the molecule is **too polar overall** (e.g., high PSA due to multiple heteroatoms + cation), it might show weaker block than expected. However, the fused aromatic system is sizable enough that many such cations still block hERG.",
